<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="321" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,325,710]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,325,350]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be separated from its congeners by the valva with a horn-shaped process at the base of costa and the juxta with a median forked process posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[886,974,361,386]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 33" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[219,1360,202,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[200,1386,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 33. Male genitalia of Scythropiodes spp. 31, S. triangulus Park et Wu, genitalia slide No. WQY 14209; 32, S. asymmetricus sp. nov.: a – c, enlarged distal portion of left valva (a, holotype, genitalia slide No. WQY 13019; b, paratype, genitalia slide No. WQY 15005; c, paratype, genitalia slide No. WQY 14136); 33, S. taedus sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide No. WQY 13023. (Scale bars = 0.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258373/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
Fig. 
<number box="[943,974,361,385]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1283,361,386]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Scythropiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulus">
<emphasis box="[999,1283,361,386]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Scythropiodes triangulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1905" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,579,397,422]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Myriopleura" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="psilotis">
<emphasis box="[151,383,397,422]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Myriopleura psilotis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick" box="[400,570,397,422]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" refString="Meyrick, E. (1905) Descriptions of Indian Micro-Lepidoptera. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 16, 580 - 619." type="journal article" year="1905">
Meyrick, 
<number box="[513,570,397,422]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" value="1905.0">1905</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in both appearance and male genitalia. The generic status of 
<emphasis box="[1294,1436,397,422]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Myriopleura</emphasis>
Meyrick remains to be further studied.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
